{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos757.erdos_757 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos757.erdos_757.","id":"vf_0afbee3beac0f907","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #757: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $A\\subset \\mathbb{R}$ be a set of size $n$ such that every subset $B\\subseteq A$ with $\\lvert B\\rvert =4$ has $\\lvert B-B\\rvert\\geq 11$. Find the best constant $c>0$ such that $A$ must always contain a Sidon set of size $\\geq cn$. Current best: Erd\\H{o}s and S\\'{o}s proved that $c\\geq 1/2$. Gy\\'{a}rf\\'{a}s and Lehel \\cite{GyLe95} proved\\[\\frac{1}{2}<c<\\frac{3}{5}.\\](The example proving the upper bound is the set of the first $n$ Fibonacci numbers.)  References  [GyLe95] Gy\\'{a}rf\\'{a}s, Andr\\'{a}s and Lehel, Jen\\H{o}, Linear sets with five distinct differences among any four elements. Prize: no. Tags: distances, geometry, sidon sets.","id":"vf_70853cc8079da99f","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/757.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_0afbee3beac0f907","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:757","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_0afbee3beac0f907","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_70853cc8079da99f","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_70853cc8079da99f","source_root":"sha256:d3db36